run nearby commands in terminal:
sudo apt install git
git clone https://github.com/debian012/ricoh-sp100su/
cd ricoh-sp100su
bash install.sh

after install open http://localhost:631/ 
then go to the "administration tab" and click "add printer" and use your local login and password of your linux user when you see pop-up login window 
add your printer RICOH Aficio SP 100SU and add your downloade ppd file "RICOH_Aficio_SP_204.ppd" (in ricoh-sp100su directory)
Thats it! ;)
